dc_description_s: 1 map ; 45 x55 cm.|Relief shown pictorially.|North oriented toward the right of the map.|Decorative cartouche includes two faces. A scale cartouche in the shape of a obelisk crowned by a fleur de lis in the bottom left corner.|This state was published in atlases by Jan Jansson in 1631-33, and 1637.|From the Jansson Appendix Atlas 1636-1680, title created to represent a unique collection within the Clark Library, University of Michigan.
